radiographic_examinations.findings: Streaky opacities in the bilateral lung bases compatible with minimal bibasilar atelectasis. Lungs are otherwise clear. No pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver enhances homogeneously without concerning focal lesion. No intrahepatic biliary ductal dilation. Patent portal vein. No gallbladder stones or wall thickening. No peripancreatic stranding or ductal dilation. Unremarkable adrenals. No splenomegaly or focal splenic lesion. Small splenule seen inferior to the spleen. Normal symmetric nephrograms. No hydronephrosis. Non-dilated loops of small bowel are normal with no evidence of obstruction. Tubular, blind-ending structure with an 8 mm diameter in the right lower quadrant compatible with early or mild appendicitis. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. Normal caliber abdominal aorta. No free intraperitoneal air. Peripherally enhancing, 1.8 cm hypodensity in the right adnexa compatible with a corpus luteal cyst. Trace free pelvic fluid. Normal uterus and bladder. No evidence of pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy. Minimal degenerative joint change of the thoracolumbar spine.
